search::createSearchArray()

Description
    private array search::createSearchArray(void)
    Concatenates elements of POST variables, $this->engine->cleanPost['RAW']['searchString'] and $this->engine->cleanPost['MYSQL']['bool'], passed from the 
    calling script into a variable, $keywords.  $keywords is finally converted to an array by calling search::searchStringToArray().

Return Values
    Returns an array of keywords.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$this->searchArray = $this->createSearchArray();
	...
    ?>

See Also
    search::submit()
